OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry day with long sunny
OL,6,Fspells and an increasingly brisk
OL,7,Feasterly breeze, especially over hills
OL,8,Fwhere it will likely become strong.
OL,9,FWarm inland but cooler along coasts.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA dry evening with some late
OL,12,Fsunny spells, though rather breezy. A
OL,13,Fclear night will follow, becoming
OL,14,Fchilly with a risk of rural frosts.
OL,15,FWinds easing away from hills.
OL,16,
OL,17,CThursday:FAnother day of long sunny
OL,18,Fspells, though windy once again, these
OL,19,Fstrongest near coasts. Warm, though
OL,20,Ffeeling cooler in exposed areas and
OL,21,Falong eastern coasts.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
